\par How bitter is your disaster,
\par For it reaches clear to your heart!\'94
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 19}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~O my anguish, my anguish!
\par I feel great pain in my very heart.
\par My heart pounds within me.
\par I cannot keep silent,
\par For I have heard the sound of the horn,
\par The alarm signal of war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 20}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~Disaster after disaster has been reported,
\par For the whole land has been destroyed.
\par Suddenly my own tents are destroyed,
\par In a moment my tent cloths.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 21}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~How long will I keep seeing the signal,
\par Keep hearing the sound of the horn?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 22}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~\'93For my people are foolish;
\par They take no note of me.
\par They are stupid sons, with no understanding.
\par They are clever enough when it comes to doing bad,
\par But they do not know how to do good.\'94
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 23}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~
I saw the land, and look! it was empty and desolate.
\par I looked at the heavens, and their light was no more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 24}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~I saw the mountains, and look! they were quaking,

\par And the hills were shaking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 25}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~I saw, and look! there was no man,
\par And the birds of the heavens had all fled.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 26}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~I saw, and look! the orchard had beco
me a wilderness,
\par And its cities had all been torn down.
\par It was because of Jehovah,
\par Because of his burning anger.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 27}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~For this is what Jehovah says: \'93
The whole land will become desolate,
\par But I will not carry out a complete extermination.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 28}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~For this reason the land will mourn,
\par And the heavens above will become dark.
\par It is because I have spoken, I have decided,
\par And I will not change my mind, nor will I turn back from it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 29}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~At the sound of the horsemen and the archers,

\par The entire city flees.
\par They enter into the thickets,
\par And they climb the rocks.
\par Every city is abandoned,
\par And no man dwells in them.\'94
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 30}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~Now that you are devastated, what will you do?

\par You used to clothe yourself with scarlet,
\par To deck yourself with gold ornaments,
\par And to enlarge your eyes with black paint.
\par But it is in vain that you beautified yourself,
\par For those lusting after you have rejected you;
\par They are now seeking to take your life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 31}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~
For I have heard the sound like that of a sick woman,
\par The distress like that of a woman giving birth to her first child,
\par The voice of the daughter of Zion who keeps gasping for breath.
\par She says as she spreads out her palms:
\par \'93Woe to me, for I am exhausted because of the killers!\'94
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qc \fi576\li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\fs32\cf21\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 Chapter }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 
\b\fs32\cf22\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 5
\par }\pard \ltrpar\ql \fi-432\li432\ri0\nowidctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\rin0\lin432\itap0 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 1}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~Roam the streets of Jerusalem.
\par Look around and take note.
\par Search her public squares to see
\par Whether you can find a man who acts with justice,
\par One who seeks to be faithful,
\par And I will forgive her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~Even if they say: \'93As surely as Jehovah is alive!
\'94
\par They would still swear to what is false.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~O Jehovah, do your eyes not look for faithfulness?

\par You struck them, but it made no impact on them.
\par You exterminated them, but they refused to accept discipline.
\par They made their faces harder than a rock,
\par And they refused to turn around.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 4}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~But I said to myself: \'93
Surely these must be the lowly.
\par They act foolishly, for they do not know the way of Jehovah,
\par The judgment of their God.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 5}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~I will go to the prominent men and speak with them,

\par For they must have taken note of the way of Jehovah,
\par The judgment of their God.
\par But they had all broken the yoke
\par And torn apart the restraints.\'94
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 6}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~That is why a lion of the forest attacks them,

\par A wolf of the desert plains keeps ravaging them,
\par A leopard lies awake at their cities.
\par Everyone going out from them is torn to pieces.
\par For their transgressions are many;
\par Their acts of unfaithfulness are numerous.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 7}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~How can I forgive you for this?
\par Your sons have abandoned me,
\par And they swear by what is no God.
\par I satisfied their needs,
\par But they kept committing adultery,
\par And they flocked to the house of a prostitute.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 8}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~They are like eager, lustful horses,
\par Each neighing after another man\rquote s wife.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 9}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~\'93Should I not 
call them to account for these things?\'94 declares Jehovah.
\par \'93Should I not avenge myself on such a nation?\'94
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 10}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~\'93
Come up against her vineyard terraces and bring ruin,
\par But do not make a complete extermination.
\par Take away her spreading shoots,
\par For they do not belong to Jehovah.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 11}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~For the house of Israel and the house of Judah

\par Have been utterly treacherous with me,\'94 declares Jehovah.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 12}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~\'93They have denied Jehovah, and they keep saying,

\par \lquote He will do nothing.
\par No calamity will come upon us;
\par We will not see sword or famine.\rquote 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 13}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~The prophets are full of wind,
\par And the word is not in them.
\par Let this happen to them!\'94
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 14}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~
Therefore this is what Jehovah, the God of armies, says:
\par \'93Because these men are saying this,
\par Here I am making my words a fire in your mouth,
\par And this people is the wood,
\par And it will consume them.\'94
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 15}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~\'93
Here I am bringing in on you a nation from far away, O house of Israel,\'94 declares Jehovah.
\par \'93It is an enduring nation.
\par It is an ancient nation,
\par A nation whose language you do not know,
\par And whose speech you cannot understand.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 16}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~Their quiver is like an open grave;
\par All of them are warriors.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 17}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~They will devour your harvest and your bread.

\par They will devour your sons and your daughters.
\par They will devour your flocks and your herds.
\par They will devour your vines and your fig trees.
\par They will destroy with the sword your fortified cities in which you trust.\'94
\par }\pard \ltrpar\ql \fi576\li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 18}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f1\cf24\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~\'93But even in those days,\'94 declares Jehovah, \'93I will not carry out a complete extermination of you. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 19}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf24\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~And when they ask, \lquote Why has Jehovah our God done all these things to us?
\rquote  you should answer them, \lquote Just as you abandoned me to serve a foreign god in your land, so you will serve foreigners in a land that is not yours.\rquote \'94
\par }\pard \ltrpar\ql \fi-432\li432\ri0\nowidctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\rin0\lin432\itap0 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 20}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~Declare this in the house of Jacob,
\par And proclaim it in Judah, saying:
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 21}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~\'93Hear this, you foolish and senseless people:

\par They have eyes but cannot see;
\par They have ears but cannot hear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 22}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~\lquote Do you not fear me?\rquote 
 declares Jehovah,
\par \lquote Should you not tremble before me?
\par It is I who placed the sand as the boundary for the sea,
\par A permanent regulation that it cannot pass over.
\par Although its waves toss, they cannot prevail;
\par Although they roar, they still cannot pass beyond it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 23}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~But this people has a stubborn and rebellious h
eart;
\par They have turned aside and gone their own way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 24}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~And they do not say in their heart:
\par \'93Let us now fear Jehovah our God,
\par The One who gives the rain in its season,
\par Both the autumn rain and the spring rain,
\par The One who guards for us the appointed weeks of the harvest.\'94
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 25}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~
Your own errors have prevented these things from coming;
\par Your own sins have deprived you of what is good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 26}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~For among my people there are wicked men.
\par They keep peering, as when birdcatchers crouch down.
\par They set a deadly trap.
\par It is men whom they catch.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 27}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~Like a cage full of birds,
\par So their houses are full of deception.
\par That is why they have become powerful and rich.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 28}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~They have grown fat and smooth;
\par They overflow with evil.
\par They do not plead the legal case of the fatherless,
\par That they may gain success;
\par And they deny justice to the poor.\rquote \'94
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 29}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~\'93
Should I not call them to account for these things?\'94 declares Jehovah.
\par \'93Should I not avenge myself on such a nation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 30}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~
Something appalling and horrible has occurred in the land:
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 31}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~The prophets prophesy lies,
\par And the priests dominate by their own authority.
\par And my own people love it that way.
\par But what will you do when the end comes?\'94
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qc \fi576\li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\fs32\cf21\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 Chapter }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 
\b\fs32\cf22\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 6
\par }\pard \ltrpar\ql \fi-432\li432\ri0\nowidctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\rin0\lin432\itap0 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 1}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~Take shelter, O sons of Benjamin, away from Jerusalem.
\par Blow the horn in T}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf6\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 ko\u697\'5fa;
\par Light a fire signal over Beth-ha}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf6\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 che\u697\'5frem!
\par For a calamity looms from the north, a great disaster.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~
The daughter of Zion resembles a beautiful and delicate woman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~The shepherds and their droves will come.
\par They will pitch their tents all around her,
\par Each grazing the flock in his care.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 4}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~\'93Prepare for war against her!
\par Rise up, and let us attack her at midday!\'94
\par \'93Woe to us, for the day is declining,
\par For the shadows of evening are getting longer!\'94
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 5}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~\'93Rise up, and let us attack during the night

\par And destroy her fortified towers.\'94
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 6}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~For this is what Jehovah of armies says:
\par \'93Cut down wood and raise up a siege rampart against Jerusalem.
\par She is the city that must be held to account;
\par There is nothing but oppression within her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 7}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~As a cistern keeps its water cool,
\par So she keeps her wickedness cool.
\par Violence and destruction are heard in her;
\par Sickness and plague are constantly before me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 8}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~
Be warned, O Jerusalem, or I will turn away from you in disgust;
\par I will make you desolate, a land without inhabitants.\'94
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 9}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~This is what Jehovah of armies says:
\par \'93They will thoroughly glean the remnant of Israel as the last grapes on a vine.
\par Pass your hand again like one gathering grapes from the vines.\'94
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 10}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~\'93To whom should I speak and give warning?
\par Who will listen?
\par Look! Their ears are closed, so that they are unable to pay attention.
\par Look! The word of Jehovah has become something they scorn;
\par They find no pleasure in it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 11}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~So I am filled with the wrath of Jehovah,
\par And I am tired of holding it in.\'94
\par \'93Pour it out on the child in the street,
\par On the groups of young men gathered together.
\par They will all be captured, a man along with his wife,
\par The old men along with the very old.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 12}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~Their houses will be turned over to others,
\par Together with their fields and their wives.
\par For I will stretch my hand out against the inhabitants of the land,\'94 declares Jehovah.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 13}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~\'93For from the 
least to the greatest, each one is making dishonest gain;
\par From the prophet to the priest, each one is practicing fraud.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 14}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~
And they try to heal the breakdown of my people lightly, saying,
\par \lquote There is peace! There is peace!\rquote 
\par When there is no peace.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 15}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~
Do they feel ashamed of the detestable things they have done?
\par They feel no shame at all!
\par They do not even know how to feel humiliated!
\par So they will fall among the fallen.
\par When I bring punishment on them they will stumble,\'94 says Jehovah.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 16}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~This is what Jehovah says:
\par \'93Stand at the crossroads and see.
\par Ask about the ancient roadways,
\par Ask where the good way is, and walk in it,
\par And find rest for yourselves.\'94
\par But they say: \'93We will not walk in it.\'94
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 17}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~\'93And I appointed watchmen who said,
\par \lquote Pay attention to the sound of the horn!\rquote \'94
\par But they said: \'93We will not pay attention.\'94
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 18}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~\'93Therefore hear, O nations!
\par And know, O assembly,
\par What will happen to them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 19}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~Listen, O earth!
\par I am bringing calamity on this people
\par As the fruitage of their own schemes,
\par For they paid no attention to my words
\par And they rejected my law.\'94
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 20}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~\'93
What do I care that you bring frankincense from She\u697\'5fba
\par And sweet cane from a distant land?
\par Your whole burnt offerings are not acceptable,
\par And your sacrifices do not please me.\'94
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 21}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~Therefore this is what Jehovah says:
\par \'93Here I am setting for this people stumbling blocks,
\par And they will stumble over them,
\par Fathers and sons together,
\par A neighbor and his companion,
\par And they will all perish.\'94
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 22}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~This is what Jehovah says:
\par \'93Look! A people is coming from the land of the north,
\par And a great nation will be awakened from the remotest parts of the earth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 23}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~They will grab hold of the bow and the javelin.

\par They are cruel and will have no mercy.
\par Their voice will roar like the sea,
\par And they ride on horses.
\par They draw up in battle order like a man of war against you, O daughter of Zion.\'94
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 24}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~We have heard the report about it.
\par Our hands fall limp;
\par Distress has seized us,
\par Anguish like that of a woman giving birth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 25}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~Do not go out into the field,
\par And do not walk on the road,
\par For the enemy has a sword;
\par There is terror all around.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 26}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~O daughter of my people,
\par Put on sackcloth and roll in the ashes.
\par Mourn as for an only son, with bitter wailing,
\par For suddenly the destroyer will come upon us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 27}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~\'93I have made you a metal tester among my people,

