\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 9}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~The woman who bore seven children has grown faint;

\par She struggles for breath.
\par Her sun has set while it is yet day,
\par Causing shame and humiliation.\rquote 
\par \lquote And those few remaining ones of them
\par I will give to the sword before their enemies,\rquote  declares Jehovah.\'94
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 10}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~
Woe to me, O my mother, because you gave birth to me,
\par A man subject to quarrel and strife with all the land.
\par I have neither loaned nor borrowed;
\par But all of them curse me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 11}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~Jehovah said: \'93
I will surely minister to you for good;
\par I will surely intercede for you in the time of calamity,
\par In the time of distress against the enemy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 12}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~Can anyone break iron in pieces,
\par Iron from the north, and copper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 13}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~
Your resources and your treasures I will give as plunder,
\par Not for a price, but because of all your sins throughout all your territories.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 14}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~I will give them to your enemies
\par To take to a land you do not know.
\par For a fire has been ignited by my anger,
\par And it is burning against you.\'94
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 15}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~You know, O Jehovah,
\par Remember me and turn your attention to me.
\par Take vengeance on my persecutors for me.
\par Do not let me perish because of your slowness to anger.
\par Know that for your sake I bear this reproach.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 16}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~Your words were found, and I ate them;
\par And your word became to me the exultation and the rejoicing of my heart,
\par For your name has been called on me, O Jehovah God of armies.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 17}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~
I do not sit in the company of merrymakers and rejoice.
\par Because your hand is upon me, I sit alone,
\par For you have filled me with indignation.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 18}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~Why is my pain chronic and my wound incurable?

\par It refuses to be healed.
\par Will you become to me like a deceptive water supply
\par That cannot be relied on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 19}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~Therefore this is what Jehovah says:
\par \'93If you return, then I will restore you,
\par And you will stand before me.
\par If you separate what is precious from what is worthless,
\par You will become like my own mouth.
\par They will have to turn to you,
\par But you will not turn to them.\'94
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 20}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~\'93
I am making you a fortified copper wall to this people.
\par They will certainly fight against you,
\par But they will not prevail against you,
\par For I am with you, to save you and to rescue you,\'94 declares Jehovah.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 21}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~\'93
And I will rescue you from the hand of the wicked
\par And redeem you from the palm of the ruthless.\'94
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qc \fi576\li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\fs32\cf21\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 Chapter }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 
\b\fs32\cf22\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 16
\par }\pard \ltrpar\ql \fi576\li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 1}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f1\cf24\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~The word of Jehovah again came to me, saying: }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f1\cf24\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~\'93You must not take a wife for yourself, and you must not have sons and daughters in this place. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf24\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~
For this is what Jehovah says concerning the sons and daughters who are born here and concerning their mothers who give birth to them and concerning their fathers who cause their birth in this land: }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 4}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf24\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~\lquote 
They will die of deadly diseases, but no one will mourn them or bury them; they will become like manure on the surface of the ground. They will perish by the sword 
and by famine, and their dead bodies will be food for the birds of the heavens and for the beasts of the earth.\rquote 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\ql \fi-432\li432\ri0\nowidctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\rin0\lin432\itap0 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 5}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~For this is what Jehovah says,
\par \lquote Do not enter a house where a mourners\rquote  feast is held,
\par And do not go to wail or offer sympathy.\rquote 
\par \lquote For I have taken away my peace from this people,\rquote  declares Jehovah,
\par \lquote As well as my loyal love and mercy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 6}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~Both the great and the small will die in this land.

\par They will not be buried,
\par No one will mourn them,
\par Nor will anyone cut himself or make himself bald for them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 7}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~And no one will provide food for those in mourning,

\par To comfort them over their dead;
\par Nor will anyone give them the cup of consolation
\par To drink over the loss of their father or mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 8}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~And do not enter a house of feasting
\par To sit down with them to eat and drink.\rquote 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\ql \fi576\li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 9}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f1\cf24\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~\'93For this is what Jehovah of armies, the God of Israel, says, \lquote 
Here in this place, in your days and before your very eyes, I will put an end to the sounds of exultation and rejoicing, the voice of the bridegroom and the voice of the bride.\rquote 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 10}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf24\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~\'93
When you tell this people all these words, they will ask you, \lquote Why has Jehovah spoken of all this great calamity against us? What error and what sin have we committed against Jehovah our God?\rquote  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 11}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf24\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~You must reply to them, \lquote \'93Because your forefathers abandoned me,\'94
 declares Jehovah, \'93and they kept following other gods and serving them and bowing down to them. But me they abandoned, and my law they did not keep. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 12
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf24\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~And you have behaved far worse than your forefathers, and each one of you follows the stubbornness of his wicked heart instead of obeying me. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 13}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf24\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~
So I will hurl you out of this land into a land that neither you nor your forefathers have known, and there you will have to serve other gods day and night, because I will show you no favor.\'94\rquote 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 14}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf24\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~\'93\lquote However, the days are coming,\rquote 
 declares Jehovah, \lquote when they will no longer say: \'93As surely as Jehovah is alive, who brought the people of Israel out of the land of Egypt!\'94 }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 
15}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf24\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~but rather: \'93As surely as Jehovah is alive, who brought the people of Israel from the land o
f the north and from all the lands to which he had dispersed them!\'94 and I will bring them back to their land, which I gave to their forefathers.\rquote 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\ql \fi-432\li432\ri0\nowidctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\rin0\lin432\itap0 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 16}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~\lquote Here I am sending for many fishermen,\rquote  declares Jehovah,
\par \lquote And they will fish for them.
\par After that I will send for many hunters,
\par And they will hunt them down on every mountain and every hill
\par And out of the clefts of the crags.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 17}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~For my eyes are on everything they do.
\par They have not been hidden from before me,
\par Nor has their error been hidden from my eyes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 18}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~
First, I will repay the full amount due for their error and their sin,
\par For they have profaned my land with the lifeless figures of their disgusting idols
\par And have filled my inheritance with their detestable things.\rquote \'94
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 19}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~O Jehovah, my strength and my stronghold,
\par My place to flee in the day of distress,
\par To you the nations will come from the ends of the earth,
\par And they will say: \'93Our forefathers inherited utter falsehood,
\par Futility and useless things of no benefit.\'94
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 20}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~Can a man make gods for himself
\par When they are not really gods?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 21}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~\'93So I will make them know,
\par At this time I will make them know my power and my might,
\par And they will have to know that my name is Jehovah.\'94
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qc \fi576\li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\fs32\cf21\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 Chapter }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 
\b\fs32\cf22\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 17
\par }\pard \ltrpar\ql \fi576\li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 1}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f1\cf24\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~\'93The sin of Judah is written down with an iron stylus.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\ql \fi-432\li432\ri0\nowidctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\rin0\lin432\itap0 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 With a diamond point it is engraved on the tablet of their heart
\par And on the horns of their altars,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~
While their sons remember their altars and their sacred poles
\par Beside a luxuriant tree, on the high hills,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~On the mountains in the open countryside.
\par Your resources, all your treasures, I will give as plunder
\par \emdash Yes, your high places because of sin throughout your territories.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 4}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~
You will forfeit, of your own accord, your inheritance that I gave you.
\par And I will make you serve your enemies in a land you do not know,
\par For you have kindled my anger like a fire.
\par It will burn for all time.\'94
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 5}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~This is what Jehovah says:
\par \'93Cursed is the man who puts his trust in mere humans,
\par Who relies on human power,
\par And whose heart turns away from Jehovah.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 6}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~He will become like a solitary tree in the desert.

\par He will not see when good comes,
\par But he will reside in parched places in the wilderness,
\par In a salt land where no one can live.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 7}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~Blessed is the man who puts his trust in Jehovah,

\par Whose confidence is in Jehovah.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 8}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~He will become like a tree planted by the waters,

\par That sends out its roots to the stream.
\par He will not notice when heat comes,
\par But his leaves will always flourish.
\par And in the year of drought he will not be anxious,
\par Nor will he quit producing fruit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 9}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~
The heart is more treacherous than anything else and is desperate.
\par Who can know it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 10}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~I, Jehovah, am searching the heart,
\par Examining the innermost thoughts,
\par To give to each one according to his ways,
\par According to the fruitage of his works.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 11}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~Like a partridge that gathers what it has not laid,

\par So is the one who acquires riches dishonestly.
\par They will leave him in midlife,
\par And in the end he will prove senseless.\'94
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 12}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~A glorious throne, exalted from the beginning,

\par Is the place of our sanctuary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf23\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 13}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af25 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf25\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\langfenp1033\insrsid9976433 \~O Jehovah, the hope of Israel,
\par All those who abandon you will be put to shame.
\par Those apostatizing from you will be written in the dust,
